        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 11:48PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1147 PM MDT, an area of heavy snow was located along a line
extending from 14 miles northwest of Cheyenne Wells to 7 miles north
of Eads. Movement was south at 35 mph.

Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph are possible with this area of heavy snow.

Locations impacted include...
Firstview, Arapahoe, and Cheyenne Wells.

This includes Highway 385 between mile markers 136 and 169.

Visibilities will drop quickly to less than a quarter of a mile in
this area of heavy snow.

A winter weather advisory is in effect for the area. Please monitor
local media outlets and the national weather service for further
statements.

Icy roads are possible as the snow melts on the roads then quickly
refreezes.
</description>
